With these
Corsage we bring

1177
01:32:01,215 --> 01:32:03,683
We're obliged to sing

1178
01:32:03,851 --> 01:32:05,944
What the sender wrote

1179
01:32:06,120 --> 01:32:07,747
Quote

1180
01:32:08,155 --> 01:32:10,988
Oh, si, si, si, si
Mama

1181
01:32:11,158 --> 01:32:13,752
See how I love you

1182
01:32:13,928 --> 01:32:16,897
Oh, si, si, si, si
Comma

1183
01:32:17,064 --> 01:32:23,025
Say you love me too

1184
01:32:33,414 --> 01:32:35,575
Now, don't give up, my boy.

1185
01:32:35,750 --> 01:32:37,741
You're bucking the man
she thought you were.

1186
01:32:37,919 --> 01:32:40,012
-That fellow on the white horse?
-Yes.

1187
01:32:40,187 --> 01:32:42,985
-l have an instinct for--
-For what goes on in a woman's heart.

1188
01:32:43,157 --> 01:32:44,556
-l know.
-l know this.

1189
01:32:44,725 --> 01:32:48,286
Every woman wants to be swept
off her feet and carried away.

1190
01:32:48,529 --> 01:32:52,124
Tell me, just what did this bird
Lochinvar do about his gal?

1191
01:32:52,300 --> 01:32:54,461
Well, he put on his best
suit of Sunday armor...

1192
01:32:54,635 --> 01:32:57,536
...and rode up to her father's castle,
or whatever they lived in.

1193
01:32:57,705 --> 01:33:00,538
There was a dance going on,
or something...

1194
01:33:00,708 --> 01:33:04,109
...but Lochinvar rode into the patio,
or whatever they have in Scotland...

1195
01:33:04,278 --> 01:33:07,679
...and swept the girl off her feet,
onto his horse and rode off with her.

1196
01:33:07,848 --> 01:33:09,577
l think.

1197
01:33:10,251 --> 01:33:13,311
Well, l've tried everything else.

1198
01:35:25,453 --> 01:35:28,889
Robert! Robert!

1199
01:35:29,924 --> 01:35:31,949
Wait, Robert!

1200
01:35:36,430 --> 01:35:36,564
Before we go any further,
l've got to get something straight.

1201
01:35:36,564 --> 01:35:39,226
